}
```

`CreateSubViews()` calls `RemoveAll()` then `Add()` multiple times. Both `Remove` and `Add` call `SetNeedsLayout()`. But `SetNeedsLayout()` sets `NeedsLayout = true` on the view and its subviews. This should trigger a re-layout on the next layout pass.

But what if the issue is that `SetNeedsLayout` bubbles up to `SuperView`, but the `SuperView` of the SelectorBase itself needs to know about the layout change? The `SuperView` of the SelectorBase is whatever view it was added to (e.g., the Window). When the SuperView lays out, it calls `Layout()` on its subviews, including the SelectorBase. `Layout()` checks `NeedsLayout` - if it's true, it calculates the new layout.

Wait, I think the issue might be more subtle. Let me look at the `Layout()` method and when it recalculates `Dim.Auto`.

